From: 4noha
Subject: rkdrm: accept WSDISPLAYIO_SMODE so mlterm-fb can use DUMBFB
License: ISC (this patch modifies OpenBSD source and inherits ISC; see ../LICENSE-ISC)

DM250: rkdrm: accept WSDISPLAYIO_SMODE so mlterm-fb runs.

mlterm-fb (framebuffer build) switches the wsdisplay mode to
WSDISPLAYIO_MODE_DUMBFB and then draws into the raw framebuffer.
rkdrm's wsioctl does not implement WSDISPLAYIO_SMODE (-1 = ENOTTY), so
mlterm-fb cannot reach the cairo path and falls back to xcore (bitmap
fonts) — which means no CJK glyphs.

simplefb (sys/dev/fdt/simplefb.c) accepts SMODE as a no-op (return 0).
Doing the same in rkdrm lets mlterm-fb wsmmap() the framebuffer
physical address (rkdrm_wsmmap already exposes
sfb->obj->dmamap->dm_segs[0].ds_addr) and draw as DUMBFB.

Caveat: wsdisplay rasops drawing and user-space direct drawing can
collide in principle, but while mlterm-fb is running it occupies the
entire screen so wsdisplay is not painting text — no observed conflict
on DM250.

--- a/sys/dev/fdt/rkdrm.c
+++ b/sys/dev/fdt/rkdrm.c
@@ -316,6 +316,9 @@
 	case WSDISPLAYIO_LINEBYTES:
 		*(u_int *)data = ri->ri_stride;
 		return 0;
+	case WSDISPLAYIO_SMODE:
+		/* no-op (simplefb style); allows mlterm-fb to use DUMBFB */
+		return 0;
 	case WSDISPLAYIO_SVIDEO:
 	case WSDISPLAYIO_GVIDEO:
 		return 0;
